description: Come and experience incredibly fun and entertaining Vintage Swing with a Modern Twist! UNDER 18 WITH PARENT OR LEGAL GUARDIAN. Free venue parking. The Palace Band was born from an era of rum smugglers and late night cabaret, when music bubbled with swinging emotion and soul. The raw sounds of old school jazz returns with an energy that will put your feet into motion and a smile on every face, combining soaring vocals with a flash of trumpet and the thunder of drums to make the old time new again.

description: Hosted by psychologist Hillary McBride, this event is about creating the space to step outside of the ways of being a body that are structured, familiar, and prescribed, to tune into our bodily voice, and practice moving in a way that feels authentic, giving unexplored or unexpressed places inside of us form through our movement and words. The two hours will be comprised of free movement (ecstatic dance), writing, and group sharing.

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Ladies Team. Open to team members by audition only. Team Description
Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Atlanta, Seattle and Chicago. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Ladies Team. Open to team members by audition only. Team Description
Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Atlanta, Seattle and Chicago. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

description: Join us for the Salsa Caliente Annual Salsa Competition & All Ages Dance! FRIDAY, MAY 09- White Eagle Hall, 90 Dock St, Victoria Tickets on sale here! Your night will start with a beginner Salsa lesson. No partner or experience is required and all ages are welcome. We’ll start with the basics and give you enough to keep you dancing all night! There will be lots of social dancing throughout the night to Salsa, Merengue, Bachata & Cha Cha Cha. Next up is an exciting Salsa Competition. Who will be your favourite? There will be prizes for 1st, 2nd and 3rd place. While the scores are being tabulated, we’l have a special performance for you! Social dancing until after midnight to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue & Cha Cha Cha. FRIDAY, MAY 09, 2025 AMATEUR SALSA COMPETITION & ALL AGES DANCE White Eagle Hall, 90 Dock St, Victoria, BC 8:00pm Doors Open 8:30- 9:30pm Beginner Salsa Lesson- no partner/experience required 9:30- 10:30pm Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue & Cha Cha 10:30- 11:45pm Competition & performance 11:45pm- 12:30am Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue & Cha Cha Cha
location: White Eagle Polish Hall, 90 Dock St, Victoria, BC V8V 2A1, Canada

description: This event is part of our ongoing series held on the last Sunday of every month from September to May. Make sure to mark your calendars! As a community collective non-profit association, we truly value your continuous support. All funds are reinvested to improve the quality of our gatherings and to create even more memorable experiences for you. It costs approximately $4,000 to run basic events for the year, covering costs like insurance, permits, equipment, venue rentals, administration, and website maintenance. Disclaimer: Please be aware that videos and photos may be taken during our events and could be posted on social media or online later. We appreciate your understanding! Ticket Type * Select one General Student 1 Subtotal Total will be calculated at checkout Sales ended Secure payment by Square

description: West Coast Barn Dances are a group of young musicians deeply rooted in Canada’s fiddle music tradition. These monthly dances, similar to contradances, are in the tradition of old-time barn dances. With live fiddle music and tasty homemade snacks they aim to celebrate and share the joy of fiddle music, dancing, and community. All ages welcome, no experience necessary, all steps will be taught, tasty homemade snacks, lots of fun, doors at 6:00pm, dancing starts at 6:30pm, suggested donation of $10 pp (VEC members) and $12 pp (non-members), parking available.
location: 108 Niagara Street, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9 Canada

description: This week get ready to dance till the end-a the night with Enda! We mentioned him last week, so let's talk about Leon James! Born April 27, 1913, Leon joined Whitey's Lindy Hoppers, winning the prestigious 1935 Harvest Moon Ball with partner Edith Matthews. During the 1950s and 1960s he partnered with Al Minns to promote the dances they helped to pioneer, appearing at dance events, in short films and on TV, and playing a vital role in preserving the history of the dance.

event_name: UPSTAIRS ENTERTAINMENT PRESENTS - ROY ROSENFELD + KHEN (Extended set)
description: Upstairs Entertainment are proud to present world class DJ/Producers ROY ROSENFELD & KHEN. These two are joining forces for their Pacific North West debut in Victoria BC. Roy Rosenfeld is one of the most recognized names in underground electronic music. Known for his intricate productions, he is also the founder of No Drama, a label and event series dedicated to showcasing the best of the underground scene. His approach to music is driven by the belief that while genres provide structure, true artistic success lies in maintaining individuality and pushing creative boundaries. Having many top hits in the sales charts, winning contests and awards, and collaborating with some of the most respected artists, had all gained Roy massive recognition and support from major superstars, such as Solomun, Black Coffee, Dixon, Keinemusik, Lee Burridge, Guy Gerber, Maceo Plex, Richie, Hawtin, Laurent Garnier, Michael Mayer, Guy J, Hernan Cattaneo, John Digweed, Luciano, Stephan Bodzin, Joris Voorn and many others. Khen has developed a unique sound defined by deep grooves and a refined approach to production. He is also the founder of Closure, an exclusive label that serves both as a platform for carefully curated releases and the home of his radio sets. His approach to music is rooted in years of experimentation and a deep understanding of sound, balancing technical precision with creative expression. He believes that staying true to one’s artistic vision while evolving with the scene is the key to creating music that remains both personal and timeless. Most recently, he’s released massive EP and remix projects on Anjunadeep, Bedrock,Lost Miracle, TRYBESof and Vivrant with support from Kollektiv Turmstrasse, JohnDigweed, Guy J, Edu Imbernon, Cassian, Hernan Cattaneo and many more. Both Roy and Khen are key members of the Lost & Found family and have also released music on Bedrock, the iconic label founded by John Digweed, further cementing their influence in the underground electronic music scene.
location: 15 Bastion SQ, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1J1, CA

description: Vicky Yeung is coming over from Toronto to share her Lindy Hop knowledge! This workshop will focus on becoming ambidancerous through Switch dancing, and intermediate Lindy Hop concepts. You can sign up for all of the classes, or sign up a la carte. Details: Saturday, September 21st 11:30am-3:30pm Century House, New Westminster.
location: 620 Eighth ST, NEW WESTMINSTER, BC, V3M3S2, CA

event_name: Texture Your Moves for West Coast Swing
description: We will guide you through practical musicality and movement drills that will 'colour in' any pattern in your repertoire. You'll learn: +++ How you can do more styling without feeling inhibited OR being reckless. +++ How to preserve your partnership connection while still expressing yourself. +++ How to enjoy being musical even with partners who are missing skills. +++ How to respect the rules of the WCS while learning to bend them. Come learn a super practical & universal way to LEVEL UP your musicality by adding body pulse & groove to add more personality and creativity into basic patterns, then get lots of reps to practice these tactics with the appropriate connection and timing. All the while putting these skills to use immediately in your social dancing! In this workshop we are going to take your Feetwork, Bodywork and Grooves you might ALREADY know.. with your common WCS patterns. We will show you ways to texture a  Tandem Slingshot, Hustle Check, Over Rotated Under Arm Turn. Leg Sweep to a Lunge. Do you have a style you just don't like? eg. Honky Tonk blues or lyrical or 12/8 songs. Or how about Rap sections of the song or when the song goes half the speed. Or how about those pesky bastard phrases. This workshop is for you if; You have no idea how to dance differently to different genres of music, so most of your dances look or feel the same. You feel like you are just walking through patterns without any real character to your movement and you feel robotic and stiff. You can do body pulse and contra-body but they are not automatic in your dancing yet. You can't seem to make wise, deliberate choices for texturing your moves to the music. You aren’t able to make your slow tempo songs look distinct from your other genres. **Send e-transfer to reserve your spot to danceyourfreedom@gmail.com Call Jay @ (250) 886-4599 if you have any questions. Please bring shoes or socks & your own water bottle. Space is limited to 14ppl max. You do NOT need a partner!
location: 516 Quadra St, Victoria, BC V8V 3S3, Canada
price: $30 via etransfer (for 2hr workshop) $40 (if paying at the door.)

description: Get ready for a night full of rhythm, flavor, and fuego at Havana Nights – the ultimate Latin party at LevelTwo Nightclub Nanaimo! We’re bringing the tropical vibes straight to you with: 🔥 Bachata Class & Demo by Natalia & Sergio from VanIsland Dance ( www.nanaimosalsa.com )– Learn some smooth moves and dance like a pro! 💃 Afro-Fusion Dance Performance by Tania from ( www.afro-fusionsharqidance.ca ) – A live show bursting with energy and culture of African roots! 🎧 2 Live DJs –DJ Nawalita ( @BailamosNanaimo) dropping all your favorite Latin hits, and DJ Astro ( @officalastro_p) bringing the beats with a live drum twist! Dress Code: Colorful & tropical – think bold prints, bright colors, and beachy vibes! 🌴🌺 Whether you're a dance floor Queen/King or just here for the party, this night is all about good music, good people, and unforgettable memories. So grab your amigos and come party Havana-style! Let’s dance, laugh, and make it a night to remember! ¡Nos vemos en la pista!

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description: Every Friday evening, we’re putting on a dance party! Total beginners are always welcome; our drop-in beginner lesson will have you dancing in no time. Neither partner nor experience are required, but pack a spare sense of humour! Following the lesson, the dance features fantastic live music perfect for dancing the night away whether you’re mad about lindy hop, charleston, balboa, or collegiate shag.
location: Dance Victoria (2750 Quadra St, just north of Hillside)

event_name: i-Land Fest 2025 • Vancouver Island's Caribbean Carnival • Labour Day Long Weekend
description: Get ready for three days of Caribbean culture, music, and pure vibes at i-Land Fest 2025—Vancouver Island’s Caribbean Carnival! What to Expect: Live performances & top DJs bringing you the best in Caribbean music Carnival Parade w/ Costumes Kids & Game Zone Authentic Caribbean Food Beverage Garden featuring Signature Drinks Cultural vendors, art displays and Caribbean exhibits After-parties & nonstop bacchanal This family-friendly festival is FREE and open to all—so come celebrate, dance, and embrace the vibrant Caribbean spirit! i-Land Fest Highlights: FREE 3-Day Festival @ Ship Point | Aug 29-31 GLOW • The Official Kick-Off Fete 19 + | Friday, Aug 29 Carnival Parade | Saturday, Aug 30 The Official After Party 19+ | Saturday, Aug 30 More updates coming soon. Stay tuned and don't forget to invite your crew! We going HARD this year. #MadnessInDCapital
source: GREAT DANCERS COMING TO THE VICTORIA INTERNATIONAL ...
location: 812 Wharf ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1T3, CA

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Join us for the annual Salsa Caliente Amateur Salsa Competition & All Ages Dance! Your night will start with a beginner Salsa lesson. No partner or experience is required and all ages are welcome. We’ll start with the basics and give you enough to keep you dancing all night! There will be lots of social dancing throughout the night to Salsa, Merengue, Bachata & Cha Cha Cha. Next up is an exciting Salsa Competition. Who will be your favourite? There will be prizes for 1st, 2nd and 3rd place. While the scores are being tabulated, we’l have a special performance for you. Social dancing until after midnight to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue & Cha Cha Cha.

description: Join us for an all-levels balboa dance practice space every Wednesday in Victoria B.C.! We start at 7pm, but you can drop in anytime during the practice space depending on which part you're interested in. Our location at 1741 Duchess Street in a heritage home offers hardwood floors and tea. This is for you if you have something in particular you want to work on, aren't quite sure what you want to be working on or if you want a refresher on the basics. FORMAT 7-7:45pm: Check It Out/Catch Up: Haven't been to practice before? Basics a little rusty? Focused on basic balboa concepts, come to this time to get all the tools you need to feel comfortable dancing Balboa on the social floor and the rest of the practice time. 7:45-9pm: Peer-led & Open Practice: To have the most fun you should be comfortable with both basic footwork patterns, counting music, out-and-ins, come-arounds, lollies, and toss-outs. (Not quite there yet, come at 7pm and we'll get you on your way)
source: Where to Swing Dance in Victoria - Swing Victoria
location: Victoria Balboa Practice Space, 1741 Duchess St, Victoria, BC V8R 4W2, Canada
